APPENDIX B: KEY PHYSICS EQUATIONS

Acoustic Radiation Force:

F_{rad} = \frac{4\pi r^3}{3} \cdot \frac{5\rho_p - 2\rho_0}{2\rho_p + \rho_0} \cdot \nabla\left(\frac{p^2}{2\rho_0 c^2}\right)

Attenuation in Granular Media:

\alpha = \alpha_{vis} + \alpha_{therm} + \alpha_{scat} \approx \frac{\omega^2}{2\rho c^3}\left(\frac{4\eta}{3} + \zeta + \kappa\left(\frac{1}{c_v} - \frac{1}{c_p}\right)\right)

Triboelectric Charge:

q = \epsilon_0 A \frac{V}{d} \cdot \left(1 - e^{-t/\tau}\right)

Where τ depends on material properties at cryo temperatures.



AQUILA-L: WHITE PAPER - PART 2/3

Technical Architecture & Experimental Protocol

---

1.0 SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

1.1 Overall System Overview

The AQUILA-L system employs a three-phase sequential separation approach optimized for lunar permanently shadowed region (PSR) conditions. The system operates in a batch processing mode with precise timing control to maximize efficiency while minimizing energy consumption.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 AQUILA-L SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 0: SUPPORT & THERMAL MANAGEMENT              │
│  ├── Vibration-isolated platform                    │
│  ├── Cryocooler interface (10W @ 100K)              │
│  └── Multi-layer insulation (MLI)                   │
│                                                     │
│  LAYER 1: VIBRATION PLATFORM                        │
│  ├── Electrodynamic shaker (300 Hz, 50N)           │
│  ├── 2mm amplitude control                         │
│  └── Acceleration feedback (0.5g target)           │
│                                                     │
│  LAYER 2: REGOLITH BED                             │
│  ├── 2mm depth, 30×30cm area                      │
│  ├── NU-LHT-3M lunar simulant                     │
│  └── 3% water ice by mass                         │
│                                                     │
│  LAYER 3: ACOUSTIC TRANSDUCER ARRAY                │
│  ├── 8×8 PZT elements (40 kHz)                    │
│  ├── λ/2 spacing (4.25mm)                         │
│  └── Phased array control                         │
│                                                     │
│  LAYER 4: ELECTROSTATIC COLLECTION                 │
│  ├── Quadrupole electrodes (5 kV)                 │
│  ├── Gold-plated collection surface               │
│  └── Insulated feedthroughs                       │
│                                                     │
│  LAYER 5: CONTROL & MONITORING                     │
│  ├── Real-time FPGA controller                    │
│  ├── Multi-sensor array                           │
│  └── Data acquisition system                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

1.2 Key Design Parameters

Geometric Specifications:

```
Active area: 30cm × 30cm (900 cm²)
Regolith depth: 2mm (optimized for wave penetration)
Total regolith mass: ~288g (1.6 g/cm³ density)
Ice content: 8.6g (3% by mass)
Processing volume: 180 cm³ per batch
```

Acoustic Parameters:

```
Frequency: 40 kHz (primary), 20-60 kHz (test range)
Wavelength in regolith: ~4.25mm (based on v=170 m/s)
Transducer spacing: λ/2 = 2.125mm
Array configuration: 8×8 = 64 elements
Acoustic pressure: 140-160 dB SPL (target)
```

Electrostatic Parameters:

```
Field strength: 5 kV/cm (maximum)
Electrode geometry: Quadrupole (focusing field)
Collection voltage: Adjustable 0-10 kV
Collection area: 100 cm² (central region)
```

Vibration Parameters:

```
Frequency: 300 Hz (optimized for regolith fluidization)
Amplitude: 2mm peak-to-peak (0-4mm adjustable)
Acceleration: 0.5g (target for fluidization)
Duration: 10 seconds per cycle
```

1.3 Thermal Management System

Cryogenic Requirements:

```
Operating temperature: 100K (-173°C)
Temperature stability: ±0.1K during measurement
Cooling capacity: 10W continuous at 100K
Cool-down time: <4 hours from 300K to 100K
```

Thermal Design:

```
Primary cooling: Closed-cycle helium cryocooler
  - Model: SHI RDK-408D2 (10W @ 100K)
  - Cooling power: 40W at 80K
  - Input power: 1800W (AC)
  
Cold plate: Oxygen-free high-conductivity copper
  - Dimensions: 35cm × 35cm × 1cm
  - Surface finish: Diamond-turned (Ra < 0.1μm)
  - Mounting: Vibration-isolated with G10 standoffs
  
Thermal isolation: Multi-layer insulation (MLI)
  - Layers: 30 alternating aluminum/Kapton
  - Performance: <1W heat leak at 100K, 300K ambient
  
Temperature monitoring:
  - 16× LakeShore DT-670 silicon diodes
  - Accuracy: ±0.25K at 100K
  - Sampling: 10 Hz all channels
```

