2.0 COMPONENT SPECIFICATIONS

2.1 Acoustic Transducer Array

Piezoelectric Elements:

```
Material: PZT-8 (lead zirconate titanate, modified for cryo)
Dimensions: 4mm × 4mm × 1mm
Resonant frequency: 40.0 kHz ± 0.5%
Impedance at resonance: 100Ω (at 300K), 500Ω (at 100K)
Temperature range: 10K to 350K
Q factor: 1200 (at 300K), 800 (at 100K)

Array configuration:
  - Elements: 64 (8×8 grid)
  - Spacing: 37.5mm center-to-center
  - Mounting: Epoxy bonded to aluminum backing plate
  - Wiring: 40AWG silver-plated copper for minimal thermal conduction
```

Driver Electronics:

```
Amplifier: 8× Tabor Electronics 8028 (4-channel each)
  - Voltage: ±200V peak-to-peak
  - Bandwidth: DC to 1MHz
  - Output impedance: 50Ω
  
Waveform generator: National Instruments PXIe-5451
  - Channels: 8 independent
  - Sample rate: 250 MS/s
  - Resolution: 16-bit
  - Synchronization: <1ns jitter between channels
  
Impedance matching network:
  - Custom LCR network for each transducer
  - Tuned for 40 kHz at 100K
  - Automatic tuning via microcontroller
```

