Armature mass: 100g

Amplifier: APS 125
Power: 125VA
Bandwidth: DC to 10 kHz
Cooling: Forced air

Accelerometer: PCB Piezotronics 352C23
Range: ±50g
Sensitivity: 100 mV/g
Frequency response: 0.5 Hz to 10 kHz
```

Vibration Control:

```
Controller: Data Physics SignalCalc 830
  - Real-time control: 4 input, 2 output channels
  - Algorithm: Adaptive feedforward/feedback
  - Update rate: 20 kHz
  
Vibration profile:
  - Sine wave at 300 Hz
  - Amplitude: 2mm peak-to-peak (0-2mm displacement)
  - Ramp up/down: 0.5 seconds each
  - Total duration: 10 seconds per cycle
```

2.3 Electrostatic System

High Voltage Supply:

```
Model: Stanford Research Systems PS350
Voltage: 0 to +5 kV (positive), 0 to -5 kV (negative)
Current: 0 to 2 mA
Ripple: <5 mV p-p
Programming: Analog (0-10V) and digital (RS-232)

Electrode design:
  - Material: Stainless steel 316L, gold plated
  - Geometry: Hyperbolic quadrupole
  - Rod diameter: 6mm
  - Rod length: 300mm
  - Rod spacing: 80mm (center-to-center)
  
Collection surface:
  - Material: Copper, gold plated
  - Area: 10cm × 10cm
  - Bias voltage: Adjustable 0-1 kV
  - Temperature: Maintained at 100K via cold finger
```

Charge Measurement:

```
Electrometer: Keithley 6517B
Current range: 10 fA to 20 mA
Voltage range: 10 μV to 200 V
Input impedance: >2×10¹⁴ Ω
Integration time: Programmable 0.01 to 10 seconds

Faraday cup:
  - Dual-electrode design for ice/regolith separation
  - Material: Aluminum, anodized
  - Shielding: Double mu-metal shield
  - Connection: Triaxial cable for noise reduction
```

2.4 Vacuum System

Chamber Specifications:

```
Model: Custom 60cm spherical chamber
Material: 304 stainless steel
Ports: 8× 2.75" CF, 4× 4.5" CF, 1× 8" CF
Base pressure: <1×10⁻⁶ Pa (achievable)
Leak rate: <1×10⁻⁹ Pa·m³/s
Internal volume: 113 liters

Pumping system:
  - Roughing pump: Edwards nXDS10i (10 m³/h)
  - Turbo pump: Pfeiffer HiPace 80 (67 L/s)
  - Cryo pump: CTI-Cryogenics 8" (2000 L/s for water vapor)
  
Pressure measurement:
  - Pirani gauge: 10⁻³ to 1000 Pa
  - Cold cathode gauge: 10⁻⁸ to 10⁻¹ Pa
  - Capacitance manometer: 10⁻³ to 1000 Pa (accurate)
```

