3.4 Risk Mitigation for Phase 1

Risk 1: Excessive Acoustic Attenuation

```
Contingency A: Lower frequency operation (20-30 kHz)
  - Longer wavelength improves penetration
  - Requires transducer redesign
  
Contingency B: Pulsed operation
  - High-power short pulses overcome losses
  - Reduces average power
  
Contingency C: Abandon acoustic separation
  - Proceed with vibration-electrostatic only
  - Still viable path forward
```

Risk 2: Insufficient Triboelectric Charging

```
Contingency A: Enhanced charging methods
  - Corona discharge pre-charging
  - UV illumination for photoemission
  - Ion injection
  
Contingency B: Higher applied field
  - Increase to 10 kV (requires design changes)
  - Improved electrode geometry
  
Contingency C: Alternative separation mechanism
  - Magnetic separation (if ice contains impurities)
  - Dielectrophoresis (AC field manipulation)
```

Risk 3: Cryogenic Operation Issues

```
Contingency A: Component failure at low temperature
  - Redundant sensors and actuators
  - Warm redundancy for critical components
  
Contingency B: Thermal gradients affecting measurements
  - Improved thermal design
  - Active temperature stabilization
  
Contingency C: Vacuum contamination
  - Strict bake-out procedures
  - Cold traps for condensable gases
```

