APPENDIX F: CALIBRATION PROCEDURES

Acoustic System Calibration:

1. Free-field calibration in air at 300K
2. Hydrophone calibration at known distances
3. Impedance measurement at operating temperature
4. Phase calibration using reference transducer

Thermal System Calibration:

1. NIST-traceable temperature sensors
2. Heat flux calibration using known loads
3. Thermal resistance measurement of interfaces
4. Cool-down curve validation against model

Charge Measurement Calibration:

1. Standard charge injection (known capacitor discharge)
2. Leakage current measurement over 24 hours
3. Cable capacitance characterization
4. Shield effectiveness verification

