FINAL STATEMENT

This white paper represents four years of iterative development, rigorous analysis, and continuous refinement. What began as an ambitious but flawed concept for Martian water harvesting has evolved into a viable, well-defined technology for lunar resource extraction.

The AQUILA-L project stands at the intersection of scientific discovery, technological innovation, and commercial opportunity. It addresses a critical need for sustainable lunar exploration while advancing fundamental knowledge of planetary materials and processes.

We invite you to join us on this journey—as collaborators, investors, policymakers, or simply interested observers. Together, we can turn the promise of lunar resources into reality, enabling humanity's permanent presence beyond Earth.

The future is being written in the vacuum chambers and research labs today. Let's write it together.

